# OpenClaw — the one shared local-LLM model alias for all of my apps.
#
# Apps never name a raw Ollama model (qwen3.5:4b, etc.) directly. They all ask
# for "openclaw", and this file decides what that actually is. Swap the FROM
# line, re-run ./install.sh, and every app moves together — with one copy of the
# weights resident in RAM instead of each app loading its own.
#
# Current pick: qwen2.5:3b-instruct.
#   - non-reasoning (no <think> blocks) -> ~2-3s replies on the Jetson, vs
#     130s+ for qwen3.5:4b which blew past every client timeout.
#   - ~2.2 GB resident -> leaves real headroom on the 8 GB Orin Nano, so it
#     stays loaded (OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE=-1) instead of thrashing in/out of RAM.
FROM qwen2.5:3b-instruct

# Match the server runtime (-c 4096). Keep callers' temperature/prompt theirs.
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
